<item>
            <title>[FLINK-37024] Task can be stuck in deploying state forever when canceling job/failover</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-37024</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We observed that task can be stuck in deploying state forever when the task loading/instantiating logic has some issues. Cancelling the job / failover caused by failures of other tasks will also get stuck as the cancel watch dog won&apos;t work for tasks in CREATED/DEPLOYING state at present. We should make cancel watch dog cover tasks in DEPLOYING as well (no need for tasks in CREATED state has there is no real logic between&#160; CREATED-&amp;gt;DEPLOYING).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
